Creating Measures for Raleigh Police Incidents 12


Step 1 - Text file with the new measures


In the zip file that you extracted in Step 2, open the text file, Raleigh_Police_Incidents_Measures_v01.txt, that has the measures to create new measures.


Step 2 -  Create a new table


To create a new measure that will be used to hold all our measures, click Table Tools ->  New Table and paste the following syntax:


A_KeyMeasures = {1}







Step 3:  Create DAX measures


Create the following DAX measures from the text file, Raleigh_Police_Incidents_Measures_v01.txt. 

Click on the A_KeyMeasures table ->  Under Table Tools tab ->  New Measure, copy and paste a measure.

Below is an example of how to create a few of the measures.  Follow the same steps for the remainder of the DAX formulas.






Note: 

You will see warnings stating e.g., 'Column '%measure_name%' in table '%table_name%' cannot be found or may not be used in this expression.  Ignore the messages for now as the errors will go away as measures are been created successfully.  They are dependent on other measures.

If you don't see the option to add a new measure, be sure you are in the 'Table Tools' tab.  Also, be sure to click on 'New Measure' first, to avoid overwriting your previously created measure(s).


Measures should now look as follows:





Step 4:  Configure DAX measures Data Types

Set the measures with the following data types:


With Whole Numbers and select comma:
.AVG_Crime_Rate_PerDistrict
.AVG_Crimes_PerWeekDay
.AVG_Date_Diff_CasesPerDay
.AVG_Date_Diff_ShootingsPerDay
.AVG_Duration
.AVG_Major_CrimeRate_PerDistrict
.Measure_Date_Diff


With Whole Numbers and select comma (display the values in this column with commas as a thousands separator):
.Total_Case_Numbers  
.Total_City_Of_Incident
.Total_Crime_Category  
.Total_Crime_Code
.Total_Crime_Type
.Total_District
.Total_Major_Crimes
.Total_Minor_Crimes
.Total_Shooting_Crimes
.Total_Violent_Crimes
.Total_Years



With Percentage and 2 decimal places
.Major_CrimeRate%
.Shooting_CrimeRate%
.Violent_CrimeRate%
.YOY_AVG_Crimes_PerDay%
.YOY_Major_CrimeRate%
.YOY_Major_Crimes%
.YOY_Shooting_CrimeRate%
.YOY_Shooting_Crimes%
.YOY_Total_Case_Numbers%
.YOY_Total_Crimes%
.YOY_Violent_CrimeRate%
.YOY_Violent_Crimes%


When finished, save project.
